  "prompt": "What exactly is 'pins and needles?",
  "response": "\"Pins and needles\" is a common term used to describe the sensation of prickling, tingling, or numbness that occurs when blood flow to a part of the body is temporarily restricted, usually due to pressure on a nerve. This is known medically as paresthesia. \n\nWhen you sit or lay in a position that compresses a nerve, such as sitting with your legs crossed for a long time, it can disrupt the nerve's ability to send signals to the brain. This leads to the sensation of pins and needles. Once you change position and the pressure is relieved, the sensation usually goes away as normal blood flow and nerve function are restored.\n\nHowever, if the sensation of pins and needles is frequent, persistent, or accompanied by other symptoms, it could be a sign of a more serious condition such as nerve damage or a circulatory disorder, and you should consult a healthcare professional.",
